# Network Services

## Common Services

| Service | Port |
|----------|------|
| HTTP | 80 |
| HTTPS | 443 |
| DNS | 53 |
| DHCP | 67/68 |
| SSH | 22 |
| FTP | 21 |
| SMB | 445 |
| RDP | 3389 |
| NTP | 123 |

---

## Command

```bash
ss -tuln
```

Displays listening TCP and UDP ports.

---

## Importance

Understanding common network services helps IT Support engineers diagnose connectivity and application issues.
